<h2 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-NotificationService"><span class=3D"inline-comme=
nt-marker" data-ref=3D"51bd6245-3fbc-447e-871a-e2bec6385eb5">Notification S=
ervice</span></h2>
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"51bd6245-3fbc-447e-871=
a-e2bec6385eb5">To get access to slave DB, </span></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"51bd6245-3fbc-447e-87=
1a-e2bec6385eb5">Go to&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://odin.myntra.com/" class=3D"ex=
ternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">odin.myntra.com</a>&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Access&nbs=
p;=E2=86=92 DB Access&nbsp;=E2=86=92 Schema is <strong>myntra_notification<=
/strong></span></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"51bd6245-3fbc-447e-87=
1a-e2bec6385eb5">In any SQL UI Client, enter host as&nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp;<a=
 href=3D"http://myntra_notification-userslave1.mynt.myntra.com" class=3D"ex=
ternal-link" rel=3D"nofollow">myntra_notification-userslave1.mynt.myntra.co=
m</a>&nbsp;and your ODIN DB username and password.</span></li>
<li><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"51bd6245-3fbc-447e-87=
1a-e2bec6385eb5">Choose,&nbsp;<strong>myntra_notification&nbsp;</strong>DB =
to view all tables.</span></li>
</ul>
<h4 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-StatusofPublishedSMS">Status of Published SMS</h=
4>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li>Sometimes even when the status of SMS request is <strong>PUBLISHED_TO_P=
ROVIDER&nbsp;</strong>in DB, it does not mean that it has been sent to the =
user.</li>
<li>In order to confirm this, an email with relevant details like,<br>
 - Mobile Number&nbsp;<br>
 - Message Reference Id<br>
 - Timestamp the request was pushed to provider<br>
 needs to be sent to SMS service provider. These info can be obtained from =
<strong>myntra_notification.sms_details_VIEW</strong> table.</li>
<li>Gupshup support email&nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp;<a class=3D"external-link" hr=
ef=3D"mailto:enterprise-support@smsgupshup.com" rel=3D"nofollow">enterprise=
-support@smsgupshup.com</a></li>
<li>ValueFirst support email&nbsp;=E2=86=92&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:support@=
vfirst.com" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">support@vfirst.com</a>=
</li>
<li>Karix<br>
 - Instrumentation is enabled. Get the id of SMS request from&nbsp;<strong>=
myntra_notification.sms_details_VIEW</strong> table.<br><span class=3D"inli=
ne-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"93086fc2-6dec-41c7-b8ab-8ecb5d83cf66">-&nbsp=
;Query </span><em><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D=
"93086fc2-6dec-41c7-b8ab-8ecb5d83cf66">tracking_details_v2&nbsp;</span></st=
rong></em><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"93086fc2-6dec-4=
1c7-b8ab-8ecb5d83cf66">using id from sms details as</span><strong><span cla=
ss=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"93086fc2-6dec-41c7-b8ab-8ecb5d83cf=
66"> entity_id.</span>&nbsp;<br></strong>-<strong> Sample query&nbsp;</stro=
ng>=E2=86=92&nbsp;<em>select * from `tracking_details_v2` where entity_id i=
n (2991124170);</em><strong><br></strong>- If eventType column is DELIVERY =
or CLICK, it means message was delivered to user.<strong><br></strong>- If =
no rows are returned, it means instrumentation callback is not received for=
 that request yet. In such cases we can email&nbsp;<a href=3D"mailto:tech-s=
upport@karix.com" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">tech-support@kar=
ix.com</a>&nbsp;with above mentioned details.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please go through the below walkthrough video explaining the above steps=
, <a href=3D"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1xbPC1bidsbHDHSIPFSc2u3_RhTI8K=
2LX/view" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow"><span class=3D"ap-contai=
ner ap-inline"><span class=3D"uninitialized_lref_module ap-content ap-inlin=
e" data-context=3D"{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1=
xbPC1bidsbHDHSIPFSc2u3_RhTI8K2LX/view&quot;}" data-addon-key=3D"com.bilith.=
lref.confluence-gdrive" data-module-key=3D"lref-gdrive-file"></span></span>=
</a></p>
<h4 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-StatusofSpecificEmailRequest">Status of Specific=
 Email Request</h4>
<ul>
<li>To know the status of emails triggered to Notification service, pick th=
e <strong>id&nbsp;</strong>of particular request from <strong>myntra_notifi=
cation DB</strong><em><strong>=E2=86=92 email_details_VIEW&nbsp;</strong></=
em>table.</li>
<li>Query <em><strong><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"1ec=
082fd-c4c1-4128-85f4-83ac4984e32a">tracking_details_v2</span>&nbsp;</strong=
></em>using id from email details as<strong> entity_id.&nbsp;</strong></li>
<li><strong> Sample query&nbsp;</strong>=E2=86=92&nbsp;<em>select * from `t=
racking_details_v2` where entity_id in (2991124170);</em></li>
<li>There might be delay in getting the instrumentation event from SendGrid=
 as well, in those cases we can check directly from SendGrid portal<br><pre=
 class=3D"c-mrkdwn__pre">Url : <a href=3D"http://app.sendgrid.com" class=3D=
"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">app.sendgrid.com</a><br>Username: engg_erp=
_crm<br>Password: Mynt@sg123</pre><br>
 Since 2FA is enabled, ping (<a href=3D"mailto:sujan.badrinarayan@myntra.co=
m" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">sujan.badrinarayan@myntra.com</=
a> or <a href=3D"mailto:deepak.g@myntra.com" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D=
"nofollow">deepak.g@myntra.com</a>)&nbsp;to get the code and log in.<br><br=
></li>
<li>Once logged in, go to "Email Activity" page and search using email addr=
ess. All events for that email will be displayed.</li>
<li>Click on Info button for an event to get the <strong>MsgID.&nbsp;</stro=
ng>Compare it with <strong>message_id&nbsp;</strong>column in email_details=
 table.<br><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embed=
ded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"fals=
e" height=3D"273" src=3D"bf2be45f342bb585cdc3b0000d5018e4" data-image-src=
=3D"/download/attachments/131308988/Screenshot%202021-04-09%20at%204.32.47%=
20PM.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1617966214000&amp;api=3Dv2" dat=
a-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"143077443" data=
-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" dat=
a-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"Screenshot 2021-04-09 at 4.32.47 PM.png"=
 data-base-url=3D"https://confluence.myntracorp.com" data-linked-resource-c=
ontent-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"131308988" d=
ata-linked-resource-container-version=3D"57" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span>=
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-Thanos(TicketingManagementSystem)">Thanos (Ticke=
ting Management System)</h2>
<p><br></p>
<h4 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-WrongQueueNamegettingStamped">Wrong QueueName ge=
tting Stamped</h4>
<p>We are observing cases where instead of ML Queue 3 PL is getting stamped=
 and in some cases instead of 3PM queue ML is getting stamped</p>
<p><strong>Steps to debug the issue</strong></p>
<p>1.First get the Task categoryName</p>
<p>2.Check in <strong>task_categories_detail </strong>table<strong> </stron=
g>what are the conditions configured in columns of status_details,departmen=
t_details,queue_details</p>
<p>Example :&nbsp;</p>
<p>[<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp;{<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; "selectorExpression": {<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "=3D=3D": [<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "returnCourierCode",<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "ML"<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ]<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; },<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; "values": [<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "DC"<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; ]<br>
 &nbsp; }&nbsp;<br>
 ]</p>
<p>This is sample config from department_details column.Here <strong>return=
CourierCode </strong>condition is getting checked. Now check in payload of =
that particular task if <strong>returnCourierCode</strong> field is coming =
in request.Most of the times this field will be missing.Based on that ask t=
he client to pass that field</p>
<p><br></p>
<h4 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-DCCodenotcapturedinTasks"><span class=3D"inline-=
comment-marker" data-ref=3D"edf11cbb-0edd-4a17-92a3-db362fb66561">DC Code n=
ot captured in Tasks</span></h4>
<p><br></p>
<ul>
<li>Login to Pac-thanos3 machine&nbsp;</li>
<li>navigate to&nbsp; /myntra/thanos/service/releases/current/thanos-tomcat=
/webapps/myntra-thanos-service/WEB-INF/classes/crons/workFlows</li>
<li>Execute the python command :&nbsp; python SynergyAutoPopulateLmsDetails=
.py -r ml_dc_missing -t 2297 -a THANOS -c myntra &gt; mldc_missing.txt</li>
<li>check for any mentioned TaskId if <strong>deliverycenterName</strong> i=
s populated.You can check this from SA</li>
<li>If not populated then open the file name SynergyAutoPopulateLmsDetails.=
py and manually paste the TaskId.comment this line #taskIds =3D df['Task ID=
'].tolist() and uncomment below line and paste the task Id<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; task=
Ids =3D &nbsp; ["IN24012921522629536861ITP1bkkI"]</li>
<li>Now execute the same python command mentioned above.</li>
<li>Once it is executed check in the file <strong>mldc_missing.txt </strong=
>for logs to understand if any issue.</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
