<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Ask Ser=
vice desk to enable the user from Security UI Dashboard<br>
 POC:&nbsp;Service Desk</span></p>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-anchor-link" id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-Sharinguse=
rlistbasesonroles,emailsandparametersandotherdataaskrequests"></span></p>
<p><strong>Sharing user list bases on roles, emails and parameters and othe=
r data ask requests</strong></p>
<p>For sharing userList based on <strong>PII</strong> access to <strong>myn=
tra_security&nbsp;</strong>db is prerequisite.</p>
<p>DB access request can be raised from ODIN but PII access has to be separ=
ately taken</p>
<p>Once the access is taken, following queries can be run to fetch data fro=
m the security database</p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: bold;letter-spacing: 0.0px;">Search Users by=
 Role</span></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">select =
A.name as "App Name",RES.name as "Resource Name",TT.type as "Team Type Name=
",U.email as "Email Address",R.name as "Role Names",UTM.team_id "Team Id",U=
.status from user_team_mapping as UTM inner join users as U on  U.id =3D UT=
M.user_id inner join team_type TT on TT.id =3D UTM.team_type_id inner join =
roles_users as RU on RU.user_team_id =3D UTM.id inner join roles as R on R.=
id =3D RU.role_id inner join applications as A on A.idea_app_id =3D UTM.app=
lication_id inner join resources as RES on RES.id =3D UTM.resource_id  wher=
e R.name in ('role_name1','role_name2')</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p class=3D"auto-cursor-target"><strong>Search Users by Email</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">select =
A.name as "App Name",RES.name as "Resource Name",TT.type as "Team Type Name=
",U.email as "Email Address",R.name as "Role Names",UTM.team_id "Team Id",U=
.status from user_team_mapping as UTM inner join users as U on  U.id =3D UT=
M.user_id inner join team_type TT on TT.id =3D UTM.team_type_id inner join =
roles_users as RU on RU.user_team_id =3D UTM.id inner join roles as R on R.=
id =3D RU.role_id inner join applications as A on A.idea_app_id =3D UTM.app=
lication_id inner join resources as RES on RES.id =3D UTM.resource_id  wher=
e email in ('email_1','email_2')</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><br></p>
<p><strong>Search permissions associated with a role and viceversa. (PII ac=
cess not needed)</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">select =
R.name as 'Role Name',P.name as 'Permission Name' from roles_permissions RP=
 inner join permissions as P on RP.permission_id =3D P.id inner join roles =
R on R.id =3D RP.role_id where R.name in ('Role_name_1',Role_name_2')</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Sharing user assignment details for bulk role removal</strong></=
p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">select =
A.name as "App Name",RES.name as "Resource Name",TT.type as "Team Type Name=
",U.email as "Email Address",R.name as "Role Names",UTM.team_id "Team Id",U=
.status from user_team_mapping as UTM inner join users as U on  U.id =3D UT=
M.user_id inner join team_type TT on TT.id =3D UTM.team_type_id inner join =
roles_users as RU on RU.user_team_id =3D UTM.id inner join roles as R on R.=
id =3D RU.role_id inner join applications as A on A.idea_app_id =3D UTM.app=
lication_id inner join resources as RES on RES.id =3D UTM.resource_id  wher=
e (email,R.name) in (('anurag.p@myntra.com','LMS_USER'),('prateek.samaiya@m=
yntra.com','SUPER_ADMIN'))</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>by other similar queries can be created based on the requirement from th=
e above sample queries by changing the condition in where clause like shari=
ng user data based on UIDX, login_id</p>
<h2 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-RNArchive">RN Archive</h2>
<h4 id=3D"CRMIssuesRunbook-RefundstatusfromRNarchiveddata">Refund status fr=
om RN archived data</h4>
<ul>
<li><p>From the return id get the pps id from the refunds team or search th=
e returns in SA and get the pps id.</p></li>
<li><p>Search the <em><strong>ppsId</strong></em> in,&nbsp;<strong>myntra_c=
rm</strong> schema =E2=86=92&nbsp;<strong>imps_log</strong> table =E2=86=92=
 column <strong>idempotentId</strong>.</p></li>
<li><p>Copy the <strong>urnNo</strong> data&nbsp;</p></li>
<li><p>Open <strong>rnarchive</strong> DB&nbsp;</p></li>
<li><p>In the table <strong>CO$IMPS_SP</strong> search the <strong>myntra_U=
RN</strong> filed with the copied <strong>urnNo</strong></p></li>
<li><p>Share the filtered row&nbsp;<strong>imps_RRN details </strong>with t=
he corresponding<strong> myntra_action </strong>and&nbsp;<strong>myntra_sta=
tus</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
